Chemical stabilization methods are projected to dominate the market due to their cost-effectiveness and the ability to improve critical soil properties like compressibility, strength, and durability. These methods are extensively used in the construction of various infrastructure projects, ensuring the structural integrity and longevity of the built environment. Industries such as mining, oil & gas, and manufacturing are also driving the demand for soil stabilization solutions to support their operations. Soil stabilization plays a crucial role in ensuring the stability and safety of industrial sites, making it a key aspect of operational efficiency and risk management.

